This looks correct — `currentMethod = "main"` before visiting `f14`. BUT — `n.f14.accept(this, argu)` dispatches through `GJDepthFirst.visit(NodeListOptional)` which iterates calling `node.accept(this, argu)` on each `VarDeclaration`. Our `SymbolTableVisitor` does NOT override `NodeListOptional`, so it uses the default. Each VarDeclaration node then calls our `visit(VarDeclaration)` with `currentMethod = "main"`. ✓

Unless... **the `SymbolTableVisitor` is being re-entered somehow**, or `currentClass`/`currentMethod` is being mutated. Let me check `visit(ClassDeclaration)`:

