Now I have a complete picture. Here are all the bugs I found:

---

**Bug 1 — `ConstPropVisitor.getIdValue` is broken (compilation error + wrong logic)**

```java
// YOUR CODE (lines 62-74) — BROKEN:
public CPValue getIdValue(String cls, String method, String name) {
    String cur = cls;
    while (cur != null) {
        if (st.fieldsOf(cur).containsKey(name)) {
            if (name.equals("result"))   // ← leftover debug: hardcoded "result"
                return CPValue.NAC;
            // ← falls through for non-"result" fields — no return!
        }
        cur = ch.parentOf(cur);
    }
    CPValue v = getVarValue(cls, method, name);
    if (name.equals("result"))   // ← leftover debug: hardcoded "result"
        return v;
    // ← MISSING return for all other variables — COMPILE ERROR
}
```

This won't even compile. The field-check loop never returns `NAC` for non-`result` fields, and there's no final `return` statement. Fix:

```java
public CPValue getIdValue(String cls, String method, String name) {
    String cur = cls;
    while (cur != null) {
        if (st.fieldsOf(cur).containsKey(name)) return CPValue.NAC;
        cur = ch.parentOf(cur);
    }
    return getVarValue(cls, method, name);
}
```

---

**Bug 2 — `InterConstPropVisitor.buildTopoOrder` reversal is commented out**

```java
// YOUR CODE (line ~130):
// Collections.reverse(result);   // ← COMMENTED OUT
topoOrder = result;
```

Post-order DFS gives callees AFTER callers. Without reversing, callers come first — meaning `main` is analysed before `live`, so `evalMessageSend` can't fold `live`'s return value in the same pass. Uncomment the reverse:

```java
Collections.reverse(result);
topoOrder = result;
```

---

**Bug 3 — `addIfLive` has leftover debug dead code**

```java
// YOUR CODE (lines 570-577):
private void addIfLive(Set<String> liveSet, String varName, String cls, String method) {
    if (!cp.getIdValue(cls, method, varName).isConst()) {
        liveSet.add(varName);
    } else {
        if (varName.equals("result"))   // ← leftover debug: does nothing
            ;
    }
}
```

The `else` branch is harmless but noisy. Clean it up:

```java
private void addIfLive(Set<String> liveSet, String varName, String cls, String method) {
    if (!cp.getIdValue(cls, method, varName).isConst())
        liveSet.add(varName);
}
```

---

**Bug 4 — `collectCallSiteArgValues` is called in `InterConstPropVisitor` but never defined in `ConstPropVisitor`**

```java
// InterConstPropVisitor line ~150:
Map<MessageSend, List<CPValue>> argValuesAtSite = cpv.collectCallSiteArgValues(
    callerCls, callerMeth, calls);
```

This method doesn't exist in your `ConstPropVisitor`. You need to either add it or replace with the simpler direct argument lookup. The simplest fix — add this method to `ConstPropVisitor`:

```java
public Map<MessageSend, List<CPValue>> collectCallSiteArgValues(
        String cls, String method, List<MessageSend> calls) {
    Map<MessageSend, List<CPValue>> result = new IdentityHashMap<>();
    for (MessageSend ms : calls) {
        List<CPValue> vals = new ArrayList<>();
        if (ms.f4.present()) {
            ArgList al = (ArgList) ms.f4.node;
            vals.add(getIdValue(cls, method, al.f0.f0.tokenImage));
            if (al.f1.present())
                for (Enumeration<Node> e = al.f1.elements(); e.hasMoreElements();) {
                    ArgRest ar = (ArgRest) e.nextElement();
                    vals.add(getIdValue(cls, method, ar.f1.f0.tokenImage));
                }
        }
        result.put(ms, vals);
    }
    return result;
}
```

---

